66
00:28:21.404 --> 00:28:22.462
Ann.

67
00:29:31.007 --> 00:29:32.099
Jack!

68
00:29:32.976 --> 00:29:34.068
Run!

69
00:30:04.374 --> 00:30:06.001
Jack. Jack!

70
00:30:13.716 --> 00:30:14.876
Jack.

71
00:30:23.927 --> 00:30:25.895
Ann. it's okay.

72
00:30:26.729 --> 00:30:29.129
Ann. let's go.
Let's go. Come on!

73
00:30:42.412 --> 00:30:43.777
Let's go. Come on.

74
00:30:44.514 --> 00:30:45.742
Come on!

75
00:32:18.007 --> 00:32:19.099
Carl!

76
00:32:19.275 --> 00:32:21.971
Please! Somebody help us!

77
00:32:24.113 --> 00:32:25.580
They've gone.

78
00:32:27.150 --> 00:32:29.209
Carl. Christ.

79
00:32:29.786 --> 00:32:30.878
Carl!

80
00:32:31.721 --> 00:32:33.882
Drop the bridge.
Do it now. for Christ's sake!

81
00:32:33.957 --> 00:32:35.185
Not yet.

82
00:32:36.626 --> 00:32:37.718
Wait.

83
00:32:38.394 --> 00:32:39.486
Wait.

84
00:32:43.633 --> 00:32:44.725
Wait!

85
00:32:55.445 --> 00:32:56.673
Come on!

86
00:34:09.152 --> 00:34:10.642
Now!
Throw them!

87
00:34:10.720 --> 00:34:12.119
Throw!

88
00:34:12.989 --> 00:34:14.013
No!

89
00:34:16.392 --> 00:34:17.620
Hold him!

90
00:34:17.693 --> 00:34:19.183
Are you out of your mind?

91
00:34:27.904 --> 00:34:30.031
-Stop!
-Hold the line!

92
00:34:30.773 --> 00:34:32.172
Keep him down!

93
00:34:37.747 --> 00:34:38.736
Heave!

94
00:34:39.782 --> 00:34:41.113
Please!

95
00:34:41.584 --> 00:34:43.279
No! Stop!

96
00:34:43.619 --> 00:34:44.608
Jack.

97
00:34:45.688 --> 00:34:46.950
No.
Get her out of...

98
00:34:47.023 --> 00:34:48.923
They'll kill him!
There's nothing we can do.

99
00:34:48.991 --> 00:34:50.959
No!
Get her out of his sight!

100
00:34:51.027 --> 00:34:52.961
It's too late.
Throw it!

101
00:34:55.231 --> 00:34:56.323
Look out!

102
00:34:58.634 --> 00:35:00.101
Let go of me.

103
00:35:04.240 --> 00:35:05.867
We gotta go. Come on.

104
00:35:06.442 --> 00:35:07.636
Come on.
Stop it.

105
00:35:07.710 --> 00:35:09.234
Leave me alone!

106
00:35:10.413 --> 00:35:11.937
Ann. please come on.

107
00:35:19.255 --> 00:35:21.086
-Kill it!
-No. No!

108
00:35:21.290 --> 00:35:23.554
It's over.
you Goddamn lunatic!

109
00:35:25.761 --> 00:35:27.285
All of you. run!

110
00:35:27.363 --> 00:35:28.728
Come on. Come on!

111
00:35:36.906 --> 00:35:38.533
Move it! Move it!

112
00:35:40.910 --> 00:35:42.275
Come on. come on!

113
00:35:51.187 --> 00:35:52.814
Stay there!
It's me he wants!

114
00:35:52.889 --> 00:35:55.084
Please stop this!
Move! Hold onto her!

115
00:35:55.158 --> 00:35:57.820
Ann. go.
Please. I can stop this!

116
00:35:57.894 --> 00:35:59.418
No!
Ann. stay there!

117
00:36:01.898 --> 00:36:03.297
Get it out!

118
00:36:06.035 --> 00:36:07.900
Get the hell out of here!

119
00:36:07.970 --> 00:36:09.961
Come on!
Jimmy. don't be crazy!
Come on.

120
00:36:10.039 --> 00:36:11.336
Don't be crazy.

121
00:36:12.542 --> 00:36:13.634
Let me go!

122
00:36:14.977 --> 00:36:16.444
Cast off!

123
00:36:18.748 --> 00:36:20.010
Come on. Carl!

124
00:36:21.484 --> 00:36:23.315
-Row!
-Wait.

125
00:36:23.586 --> 00:36:25.713
Row. Goddamn it!

126
00:36:35.965 --> 00:36:37.091
Go back.

127
00:36:44.006 --> 00:36:45.132
Jimmy. no!

128
00:36:52.114 --> 00:36:53.103
No!

129
00:37:10.199 --> 00:37:12.030
No! Don't! Leave him alone!

130
00:37:12.101 --> 00:37:13.625
Hide out in the back!

131
00:37:36.192 --> 00:37:37.819
Wait!
No!

132
00:37:38.527 --> 00:37:41.121
No! No! Please don't!

133
00:39:39.348 --> 00:39:41.873
The whole world
will pay to see this.

134
00:39:44.620 --> 00:39:46.611
We're millionaires. boys!

135
00:39:46.922 --> 00:39:48.822
I'll share it with all of you!

136
00:39:49.658 --> 00:39:54.152
In a few months
his name will be up
in lights on Broadway!

137
00:39:56.332 --> 00:40:00.428
Kong!
The Eighth Wonder
of the World!

138
00:41:03.732 --> 00:41:05.757
What can I say?
What can I say?

139
00:41:05.835 --> 00:41:07.234
Any comments. sir?

140
00:41:08.571 --> 00:41:10.198
The Mayor. thank you.

141
00:41:11.407 --> 00:41:12.396
Ready.

142
00:41:12.575 --> 00:41:13.906
What am I?

143
00:41:14.310 --> 00:41:16.039
Thank you very much.

144
00:41:19.882 --> 00:41:21.372
Get used to it.

145
00:41:21.584 --> 00:41:23.245
Listen. great to see you.
Ready?

146
00:41:23.319 --> 00:41:24.786
I'm really
appreciating that...

147
00:41:24.854 --> 00:41:26.321
Look at you!
I remember you.

148
00:41:26.388 --> 00:41:29.380
You're a lucky guy. Denham.
Am I a lucky guy?

149
00:41:29.458 --> 00:41:31.255
Maybe you're the lucky guy.

150
00:41:45.074 --> 00:41:46.234
Carl!

151
00:41:48.110 --> 00:41:49.304
Zelman!
I told you.

152
00:41:49.378 --> 00:41:50.845
I know you did
and I appreciate it.

153
00:41:50.913 --> 00:41:52.904
Let's get a shot of this.

154
00:41:53.382 --> 00:41:54.508
Come on.

155
00:41:55.251 --> 00:41:57.583
Big smile.
Yeah! That's great!

156
00:41:59.955 --> 00:42:02.890
<i>Look at yourself.
Look at what you've become.</i>

157
00:42:03.626 --> 00:42:06.151
-No woman is worth this.
-This woman is worth it.

158
00:42:06.228 --> 00:42:08.219
I don't care what it takes.
I gotta win her back.

159
00:42:08.297 --> 00:42:09.525
Oh. really?

160
00:42:09.598 --> 00:42:11.259
She's not gonna buy this
for a second.

161
00:42:11.333 --> 00:42:13.528
Shut up and hand me
the grapefruit!

162
00:42:15.671 --> 00:42:18.333
<i>-You're writing a comedy?
-Yes. I am.</i>

163
00:42:19.074 --> 00:42:21.008
<i>I'm writing it for you.</i>

164
00:42:22.945 --> 00:42:24.810
<i>Why would you do that?</i>

165
00:42:25.814 --> 00:42:28.214
<i>Why would I write
a play for you?</i>

166
00:42:31.620 --> 00:42:33.247
<i>Isn't it obvious?</i>

167
00:42:33.522 --> 00:42:35.012
Oh. I'm sorry.

168
00:42:36.258 --> 00:42:38.123
I couldn't help but overhear.

169
00:42:41.630 --> 00:42:44.360
So. he took me to this
fancy French restaurant...

170
00:42:44.433 --> 00:42:47.231
and halfway through
the hors d'oeuvres.
he clutches my hand.

171
00:42:47.303 --> 00:42:49.498
And that's when he told you
how he felt?

172
00:42:49.572 --> 00:42:52.302
No. He never said it.
He never said it?

173
00:42:52.374 --> 00:42:54.342
He probably thought
he didn't need to say it.

174
00:42:54.410 --> 00:42:56.435
Well. then how does she know
that it's real?

175
00:42:56.512 --> 00:42:59.970
He said it was
not about the words.
Oh. please!

176
00:43:00.182 --> 00:43:04.312
If you feel it. you say it.
It's really very simple.

177
00:43:04.687 --> 00:43:08.987
He said we'd talk
about it later.
Only there was no later.

178
00:43:10.726 --> 00:43:12.284
It never happened.

179
00:43:13.295 --> 00:43:15.058
That's how it ended.

180
00:43:15.197 --> 00:43:18.928
He just let you walk away?
He didn't try to save it?

181
00:43:20.803 --> 00:43:24.170
I honestly believed
things might actually
work out...

182
00:43:25.274 --> 00:43:27.265
which was really very...

183
00:43:30.546 --> 00:43:31.774
foolish.

184
00:43:32.014 --> 00:43:34.642
Men.
Oh. they'll give you
the world...

185
00:43:34.717 --> 00:43:37.117
but they let the one thing
that truly matters...

186
00:43:37.186 --> 00:43:39.086
slip through their fingers.

187
00:43:39.154 --> 00:43:40.382
Typical.

188
00:43:40.990 --> 00:43:44.653
They're so busy being brave.
they forget to use
their brains.

189
00:43:45.628 --> 00:43:47.528
Romance. Who needs it?

190
00:44:12.287 --> 00:44:13.618
Thank you.

191
00:44:14.456 --> 00:44:15.821
Thank you.

192
00:44:18.761 --> 00:44:20.092
Thank you.

193
00:44:21.897 --> 00:44:23.262
Thank you.

194
00:44:25.067 --> 00:44:26.534
Ladies and gentlemen...

195
00:44:28.137 --> 00:44:30.628
I'm here to tell you
a very strange story.

196
00:44:31.407 --> 00:44:33.136
The story of our adventure...

197
00:44:33.976 --> 00:44:36.945
in which 17 of our party
suffered horrible deaths...

198
00:44:37.913 --> 00:44:39.403
their lives lost...

199
00:44:40.182 --> 00:44:42.275
in pursuit of
a savage beast...

200
00:44:43.452 --> 00:44:46.046
a monstrous aberration
of nature.

201
00:44:47.289 --> 00:44:49.416
But even the meanest brute
can be tamed.

202
00:44:50.159 --> 00:44:52.457
Yes. ladies and gentlemen.
as you will see...

203
00:44:52.928 --> 00:44:54.589
the beast was no match...

204
00:44:55.197 --> 00:44:56.755
for the charms of a girl.

205
00:45:00.235 --> 00:45:01.827
A girl from New York...

206
00:45:05.040 --> 00:45:06.837
Who melted his heart...

207
00:45:07.543 --> 00:45:10.137
bringing to mind
that old Arabian proverb...

208
00:45:12.081 --> 00:45:15.244
"And lo. the beast looked
upon the face of beauty...

209
00:45:16.285 --> 00:45:18.185
"and beauty stayed his hand.

210
00:45:19.488 --> 00:45:23.356
"And from that day forward.
he was as one dead."

211
00:45:31.133 --> 00:45:34.591
And now. ladies and gentlemen.
I'm going to show you...

212
00:45:34.737 --> 00:45:37.729
the greatest thing
your eyes have ever beheld.

213
00:45:38.874 --> 00:45:43.538
He was a king in the world
he knew. but he comes to you
now a captive.

214
00:45:44.747 --> 00:45:46.408
Ladies and gentlemen...

215
00:45:46.482 --> 00:45:51.010
I give you Kong.
The Eighth Wonder
of the World!

216
00:46:00.395 --> 00:46:03.523
Don't be alarmed.
It's perfectly safe.

217
00:46:03.832 --> 00:46:07.268
These chains are made
of chrome steel!

218
00:46:28.023 --> 00:46:29.820
Observe. if you will...

219
00:46:33.095 --> 00:46:35.063
I am touching the beast.

220
00:46:35.364 --> 00:46:39.596
I am actually laying my hand
on the 25-foot gorilla.

221
00:46:46.742 --> 00:46:48.369
Crank 'em up. fellas.

222
00:47:07.696 --> 00:47:09.891
And now. we have
in the auditorium tonight...

223
00:47:09.965 --> 00:47:11.592
a surprise guest.

224
00:47:12.401 --> 00:47:14.596
The real-life hero
of this story.

225
00:47:15.003 --> 00:47:17.437
The man who hunted down
the mighty Kong!

226
00:47:19.107 --> 00:47:23.874
The man who risked all
to win the freedom
of a helpless female.

227
00:47:25.047 --> 00:47:27.379
A big hand for
Mr. Bruce Baxter!

228
00:47:33.255 --> 00:47:35.314
Thank you. Thank you.

229
00:47:35.991 --> 00:47:37.151
Thank you.

230
00:48:04.853 --> 00:48:06.286
He was right.

231
00:48:07.856 --> 00:48:10.654
About there still being some
mystery left in this world...

232
00:48:11.827 --> 00:48:14.125
and we can all have
a piece of it...

233
00:48:14.496 --> 00:48:16.760
for the price
of an admission ticket.

234
00:48:18.333 --> 00:48:20.631
That's the thing you come
to learn about Carl.

235
00:48:22.738 --> 00:48:26.139
His unfailing ability
to destroy the things
he loves.

236
00:48:40.589 --> 00:48:43.183
Please remain calm.
ladies and gentlemen...

237
00:48:43.258 --> 00:48:46.557
for we now come
to the climax of
this savage ritual.

238
00:48:46.762 --> 00:48:49.253
The sacrifice
of a beautiful young girl.

239
00:48:50.032 --> 00:48:53.661
Behold her terror as she is
offered up to the mighty Kong!

240
00:48:54.903 --> 00:48:58.964
A big hand. folks.
for the bravest girl
I've ever met!

241
00:48:59.708 --> 00:49:00.970
Miss Ann Darrow.

242
00:49:48.957 --> 00:49:50.686
Save me from the beast!

243
00:49:59.568 --> 00:50:00.796
Help me!

244
00:50:04.940 --> 00:50:06.237
Where is she?

245
00:50:07.409 --> 00:50:08.967
Where's Ann?
I have no idea.

246
00:50:09.044 --> 00:50:12.445
I heard he offered her
all kinds of money
and she turned him down flat.

247
00:50:58.260 --> 00:50:59.591
Here's your story. boys.

248
00:50:59.661 --> 00:51:02.755
"Beauty and the man
who saved her from the beast."

249
00:51:08.503 --> 00:51:09.492
No.

250
00:51:17.846 --> 00:51:19.711
We have to get these people
out of here.

251
00:51:19.781 --> 00:51:21.772
Everyone needs to leave. okay?
Come on.

252
00:51:23.518 --> 00:51:25.713
Let him roar.
It makes a swell picture.

253
00:51:27.556 --> 00:51:28.580
Head for the exits.

254
00:51:28.657 --> 00:51:31.091
Get your own seat. buddy.
You're not having mine.

255
00:51:39.267 --> 00:51:40.495
Excuse me. fellows.

256
00:51:41.436 --> 00:51:44.132
Coming through.
Coming through. fellows.

257
00:51:47.709 --> 00:51:50.701
Get me down! Help me. please!

258
00:51:53.115 --> 00:51:56.016
Somebody! Somebody help me!

259
00:51:59.421 --> 00:52:02.083
Go! Go! Get out!

260
00:52:06.061 --> 00:52:07.551
Go! Go!

261
00:53:42.557 --> 00:53:44.548
There they are.

262
00:53:57.806 --> 00:53:59.467
-Go!
-Wait for me!

263
00:54:00.375 --> 00:54:01.740
Go back!

264
00:54:08.750 --> 00:54:10.012
This way!

265
00:54:17.792 --> 00:54:18.952
Help!

266
00:54:27.369 --> 00:54:28.358
No!

267
00:55:08.276 --> 00:55:10.938
Taxi! Follow that ape.

268
00:55:11.012 --> 00:55:12.502
Come on. pal.
we gotta draw him off.

269
00:55:12.580 --> 00:55:14.411
It's all yours. buddy.

270
00:55:30.832 --> 00:55:32.561
Hey. get out of here. lady!

271
00:55:53.288 --> 00:55:54.516
Come on.

272
00:56:03.698 --> 00:56:04.687
Buddy!

273
00:56:06.034 --> 00:56:08.264
Come on. Come on.

274
00:56:21.649 --> 00:56:22.638
Look out.

275
00:56:45.306 --> 00:56:46.534
Jesus Christ.

276
01:02:10.098 --> 01:02:11.190
Fire!

277
01:02:13.601 --> 01:02:14.693
Stop!

278
01:02:40.762 --> 01:02:42.320
No. No.

279
01:05:13.881 --> 01:05:15.212
Beautiful.

280
01:05:21.656 --> 01:05:22.714
Yes.

281
01:05:25.359 --> 01:05:26.724
Yes. it is.

282
01:10:23.257 --> 01:10:24.383
Hey! Hey!

283
01:10:24.658 --> 01:10:26.285
Nobody past this point.

284
01:10:27.528 --> 01:10:29.155
You can't go in there!

285
01:10:30.497 --> 01:10:31.486
Hey!

286
01:10:33.601 --> 01:10:34.898
Stop him!

287
01:10:38.005 --> 01:10:40.269
Hey! Get back.
You're not allowed up there!

288
01:10:40.341 --> 01:10:42.002
-What's going on?
-Go!

289
01:14:23.897 --> 01:14:25.194
No!

290
01:14:26.366 --> 01:14:28.527
No!

291
01:14:35.509 --> 01:14:38.137
Please! No!

292
01:14:38.512 --> 01:14:39.706
No!

293
01:17:36.323 --> 01:17:38.621
Ann. Ann.

294
01:18:27.941 --> 01:18:29.238
Move along.

295
01:18:29.710 --> 01:18:31.610
Just one shot! One shot!

296
01:18:32.279 --> 01:18:34.372
Come. come!
Boys. how about a photo?

297
01:18:34.448 --> 01:18:35.437
Look at me.

298
01:18:35.549 --> 01:18:37.278
Come on. watch the camera.

299
01:18:40.120 --> 01:18:41.644
Come a little closer.

300
01:18:42.322 --> 01:18:44.517
That's it. folks.
Show's over. Step back!

301
01:18:44.591 --> 01:18:46.786
Clear the area. That's it.
Shove off. boys.

302
01:18:47.494 --> 01:18:49.052
Why'd he do that?

303
01:18:49.362 --> 01:18:51.830
Climb up there
and get himself cornered.

304
01:18:51.898 --> 01:18:54.230
The ape must have known
what was coming.

305
01:18:54.301 --> 01:18:56.963
He's just a dumb animal.
Didn't know nothing.

306
01:19:03.176 --> 01:19:05.906
What does it matter?
Airplanes got him.

307
01:19:08.482 --> 01:19:10.450
It wasn't the airplanes.

308
01:19:14.821 --> 01:19:17.119
It was beauty
killed the beast.

309
01:19:18.305 --> 01:20:18.441
